HEADWORD: dumb-bell
<hw>dumb"-bell`</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>An exercising weight, consisting of two spheres or
spheroids, connected by a short bar for a handle; used (often in pairs)
for gymnastic exercise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An ignorant or foolish person.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> dummy, dope, boob, booby, pinhead.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>dumbfound</ent>⟦br⟧
